                <ul class="bullet-list">
                  <li><strong>Activity:</strong> Cluster care to allow rest; monitor SpO₂/HR/dyspnoea before, during, after activity; coach pursed-lip breathing during exertion; PT consult when medically stable</li>
                  <li><strong>Anxiety:</strong> Calm, reassuring presence; handheld fan to face (V2 trigeminal branch — evidence-based); coach PLB; limit clinicians in room; reduce environmental stimuli; discuss PRN anxiolytic with supervising RN (respiratory risk in COPD)</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="col-card">
                <h3 class="col-title">Dx 5 — Deficient Knowledge &amp; Dx 6 — Risk for Infection</h3>
                <ul class="bullet-list">
                  <li><strong>Knowledge:</strong> Assess understanding before teaching; use teach-back for inhaler technique; pictographic written instructions; "ABCD" warning signs; social work referral for prescription assistance; pulmonary rehab referral pre-discharge</li>
                  <li><strong>Infection:</strong> Standard + droplet precautions until source determined; hand hygiene; monitor WBC/temp/sputum; administer antibiotics on schedule; review culture results for de-escalation; document immunisation status</li>
                </ul>
